<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-03T15:22:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-03T15:22:00-05:00" n="497" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2390½: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Terre Haute, Ind.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-03T14:22:00-06:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1916—4:22 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:45 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Please hold message suggested yesterday until I can see you or if it has
                            been sent send word to await further instructions. Will explain when I
                            reach Washington.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>